_memo and st.experimental_singleton support widget replay. Fundamentally, the behavior of a function with (supported) widgets in it doesn't change when it is decorated with @st.experimental_memo or @st.experimental_singleton . The only difference is that the function is only executed when we detect a cache "miss". Supported widgets All input widgets are supported in cache-decorated functions. The following is an exhaustive list of supported widgets: st.button st.camera_input st.checkbox st.color_picker st.date_input st.download_button st.file_uploader st.multiselect st.number_input st.radio st.selectbox st.select_slider st.slider st.text_area st.text_input st.time_input Previous: st.cache_resource Next: st.experimental_singleton forum Still have questions? Our forums are full of helpful information and Streamlit experts. Home Contact Us Community Â© 2024 Snowflake Inc. Cookie policy forum Ask AI

